response.headline: Korean Traditional Medicine clinic claims to fix facial asymmetry permanently from root cause vs temporary Western treatments
response.summary: Ourkenza shares experience with Duna Korean Traditional Medicine clinic near Seongsu Station. Doctor promised permanent asymmetry fix addressing root causes versus dentist saying it's impossible and dermatologist recommending repeated botox/lifting treatments every 6 months.

extracted_text: I tried fixing my asymmetry through Korean Traditional Medicine
Few years ago, my dentist told me that fixing asymmetry was impossible even if I get braces and that I had to embrace it for the rest of my life
My dermatologist told me that we can get it fixed by lifting treatments and botox, that should be done at least once every 6months
But the doctor at Duna Korean Traditional Medicine was like: 'Don't worry, I'll fix it from the root cause so not only you can enjoy a symetrical face, but also a well balanced body forever'
image_details.key_interest: Korean Traditional Medicine approach to permanent asymmetry correction
visual_hierarchy: Main overlay text about fixing asymmetry
Person examining face in mirror reflection
